And here's an example of rejecting a Promise:

```typescript
public async connect() {
    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
        try {
            console.log('connect function called');
            this.connection = await new Promise((resolveInner, rejectInner) => {
                setTimeout(() => resolveInner(true), 2000);
            });
            console.log('connection established');
            resolve();
        } catch (error) {
            console.error(error);
            reject(error); // Reject the Promise
        }
    });
}
```

You can then handle the error in the calling code like this:

```javascript
try {
    await db.connect();
} catch (error) {
    console.error('Error connecting to database:', error);
}
